import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_counts = data.groupby('group')['person'].count().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='group', y='person', data=group_counts, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of persons across the different groups?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Group')
    plt.ylabel('Count of Persons')
    plt.legend(title='Groups', loc='upper right', labels=group_counts['group'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_counts = data['group'].value_counts(normalize=True)
    labels = group_counts.index
    sizes = group_counts.values

    plt.pie(sizes, labels=labels, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    plt.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the most common group that persons are associated with?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_counts = data.groupby('group')['person'].count().reset_index()
    group_counts.columns = ['group', 'count']
    avg_count = group_counts['count'].mean()

    ax = sns.barplot(x='group', y='count', data=group_counts)
    plt.axhline(avg_count, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_count:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average number of persons in each group?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Group')
    plt.ylabel('Count of Persons')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_count = data.groupby(['group', 'person']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    chart = sns.barplot(x='group', y='count', hue='person', data=data_count, palette='deep')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of persons across the different groups, by name?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Person', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
